Results.ReviewText:
Before I can write this review I first need to go make a fresh one. Hold on!!! Right, I'm back.... I'm a busy guy and always on the go. So, the first thing that got my attention was that they come in cups. Perfect for when you want to grab a coffee and hit the road, so already a big thumbs up there! Now, my car is great for cupholders. My cupholders grab the cup and hold it in place. However, yesterday's visit to a major coffee retailer (I won't mention names) didn't end too well. About a mile down the road and a few bumps (already some coffee spillage) the lid wouldnt stay on the cup, maybe my car was squeezing the cup to tight. However, for Nescafe Azera, this isn't an issue. First the lid has a cool close feature resulting in zero coffee spillages. Second the lid fits securely onto the cup, no problems there.

Moving onto the coffee, well that is what we are here for. The coffee is great! It certainly gives the major coffee retailers a run for their money. The latte is frothy and doesn't lack flavour, it certainly is a premium coffee. The portion amount is perfect, which I'd say is identical to a regular coffee at other retailers.

To put it simply, you get a great coffee in an equally as great cup.
Results.Title: I love them a Latte

Results.ReviewText: I noticed this product on sale within my local supermarket on a special deal and also was aware of the recent TV ads so decided to purchase as i am a great latte fan and liked the concept of the product. having tried the first cup from the pack yesterday, i can confirm the coffee is indeed delicious, no faults at all however my gripe would b3e with the cup lid. The open and close "slider" did not "slide" open and closed very easily at all and ended up having to take the lid off and on to drink at times. I think the build of heat and pressure effects this system and could have been better designed especially as this is a big part of the products selling point !
Results.Title: Great Coffe, shame about the lid !
